Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with language drift and communication protocols between agents. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of pre-trained agents and goal-based tasks. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of training constraints to improve communication performance. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of visual grounding to mitigate language drift. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is also relevant as the paper discusses multi-agent communication games and the use of non-linguistic rewards in goal-based tasks, which are relevant to robotics applications.
